body:
_Part of #9277 Access a key with Keycard epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)_

Currently, the screen layout is implemented with several bugs.

- The error message should be shown according to Figma. 
- In the current build, the "wrong passcode" error message is sometimes shown even if no pairing code has been entered (for instance, when canceling the process, and starting again);
- The error message should be shown according to Figma. 
- The error message say "Wrong code" and select the pairing code, to help users enter a different pairing code without having to manually erase the incorrect one;
- The layout should be fixed according to Figma. The pairing code is vertically and horizontally centered;
- The keyboard should never disappear on this screen;
- There should only be "Next >" in the toolbar, no "< Back";

- After the incorrect pairing code is erased, the "Wrong code" error should disappear. This is especially important on small screens since there the error tooltip might overlap the subheading;
- On smaller screens, the layout should be similar to seed phrase confirmation in onboarding, see https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/9370 for detailed specification;

